Creating a simple REST API using Node.js and Express is straightforward. Here's a basic guide:

1. Install Node.js and npm
2. Create a new project directory
3. Initialize the project with `npm init -y`
4. Install Express: `npm install express`
5. Create an `app.js` file with the following code:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
const port = 3000;

app.use(express.json());

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello World!');
});

app.listen(port, () => {
  console.log(`Server running at http://localhost:${port}`);
});
```

This creates a basic server with a single GET route. You can add more routes and functionality as needed.

